      "body" : "@laanwj I believe it's a Qt issue. They tightened the requirements with newer qt versions, -fPIE used to compile fine. But -fPIE + gcc5 + older Qt will still likely cause problems regardless if it does compile.\r\n\r\nSo the real issue is -fPIE + newer gcc regardless of when qt tightened the error. I think it makes sense to always fall back to -fPIC any time that reduce_relocations was used. The alternative would be a blacklist/whitelist for compilers, which i was trying to avoid.",
